.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-10-7::.
There 4 different types of food: grapes, kale, apricot, nectarine
The people have 4 different jobs:  engineer, architect, mechanic, bartender
4 different pets are kept: mouse, snake, fish, goat
 1. the person eating nectarine is not to the left of the person eating apricot##8
 2. the engineer is between the owner of the mouse and the person eating nectarine##2
 3. the owner of the fish is on the left or right of the bartender##3
 4. the person eating nectarine is somewhere between the person eating kale and the owner of the snake##7
 5. the owner of the snake and the person eating grapes have the same parity positions##9
 6. the architect is on the left of the owner of the snake##1
 7. the mechanic is on the left or right of the owner of the goat##3
 8. the owner of the fish is on the left of the person eating kale##1
 9. the owner of the mouse is the engineer or the owner of the mouse is the person eating apricot, but not both##10
10. the owner of the mouse and the architect have the same parity positions##9

.:: Answer ::.
|        |     1     |     2      |       3        |     4      |
| Food   | apricot    | grapes     | nectarine         | kale |
| Job    | architect | engineer    | mechanic | bartender    |
| Pet    | mouse      | snake | fish            | goat   |

